title: Gägõs
body:
The twelve Gägõs are:

  • Ãdon (Iydon)
  • Iþem (Ithem)
  • Öçak (Orchak) - Disavowed
  • Ägüg (Argoog)
  • Ũnep (Oeinep)
  • Otup
  • Ëpet (Erpet)
  • Işĩv (Isheevf)
  • Eðok (Edthok) - Disavowed
  • Ĩdẽr (Eedayr)
  • Ovoþ (Ovfoth) - Disavowed
  • Iðeç (Idthech) - Disavowed


Four of the twelve Gägõs rejected the inclusion of the Baskiþa, and as punishment they were branded with a pair of horns upon their upper back to highlight that, unlike the Hagaþisk and the Baskiþa, they lacked horns, and were therefore the weakest of the Tripartite.
preface: The Gägõs (Gargoyles) were created by Urünĩn to fight against the other Spirits.
